#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.51-62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 6. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga → gaṅgādipeyyālo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:0.2"
msgid "6. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga "
msgstr "6. Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 51–62. Gaṅgānadīādisuttadvādasaka → gaṅgādisuttāni (bj)
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:0.3"
msgid "51–62. Gaṅgānadīādisuttadvādasaka "
msgstr "51–62. Twelve Discourses on the Ganges River, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east. "

msgctxt "sn47.51-62:1.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāvento cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four kinds of mindfulness meditation slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāvento cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant who develops the four kinds of mindfulness meditation slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment? "

msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.5"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāvento cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti vitthāretabbaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four kinds of mindfulness meditation slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:2.7"
msgid "Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo chaṭṭho. "
msgstr "(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.) "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:3.1"
msgid "Cha pācīnato ninnā, "
msgstr "Six on slanting to the east, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:3.2"
msgid "cha ninnā ca samuddato; "
msgstr "and six on slanting to the ocean; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:3.3"
msgid "Ete dve cha dvādasa honti, "
msgstr "these two sixes make twelve, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.51-62:3.4"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr "and that’s how this chapter is recited."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
